                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d329">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3–949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-03-11T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 11, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>332. For Merchant. Urtels 61 Mar 9 from Taipei and 846 Mar 11 from Shanghai. Dept
                    believes you must have certain latitude dealing with problem. If Amb concurs ur
                    views re desirability appointment Sun, you might suggest he approach Act Pres
                    this matter. Seems preferable you not be involved in approach in order avoid
                    prejudice ur position if Chen not replaced.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
